                        <label class="switch">
                            <input type="checkbox" class="dsSlider" data-attribute="hpdEnable">
                            <span class="slider round"></span>
                        </label>
                        <div class="hint">DreamScreen will automatically switch to a source when plugged in.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div id="usbPowerDetectDS" class="border border-left">
                        <h5>USB Power Detect <span class="material-icons hintbtn">help_outline</span></h5>
                        <label class="switch">
                            <input type="checkbox" class="dsSlider" data-attribute="usbPowerEnable">
                            <span class="slider round"></span>
                        </label>
                        <div class="hint">DreamScreen will automaticall switch to sleep mode if the USB port connected to the TV turns off. Use a standard Micro USB cable to connect your DreamScreen hub to the TV.</div>
                    </div>
                    <div id="cecPowerDetectDS" class="border border-left">
                        <h5>CEC Power Detect <span class="material-icons hintbtn">help_outline</span></h5>
                        <label class="switch">
                            <input type="checkbox" class="dsSlider" data-attribute="cecPowerEnable">
                            <span class="slider round"></span>
                        </label>
                        <div class="hint">Allow for television to turn off DreamScreen lights via CEC. This feature will require your television to have CEC capability and for the option to be enabled in television settings. Typicall, TVs send out an OFF command but do not necessarily send out an ON command. If this is the case, disable tis feature and use USB Power Detect.</div>
